content:
Dobrý den,

nevím, proč se obrázky u některých "Produktů" nezobrazují a místo obrázku je tam jen ikona "fotoaparátu", i když je obrázek uložen aprohlížeč Firefox je nastaven, jako výchozí - viz: www.tobex.cz/cyklo ložiska - ložisko dvořadé 3801 2rs aj. -viz: https://www.tobex.cz/kulickova-loziska-dvourada (lozisko 3800 2rs max) Správce serveru jsme požádali, aby tam obrázky doplnil, ale chtěl za to vysokou částku a tak jsme tam fotky ke všem produktům doplnili sami již v r. 2024. Nevím, zda to není od nej nějaký ajťácky naschvál a proto to trvá na Googlu tak dlouho.

Děkuji za info a přeji Vám úspěšný den. Mgr. Miroslav Kňažek

title: Problem
content:
A secure webpage will have an address that begins with https:// and a lock icon Fx89Padlock in the address bar. If a login page you're viewing does not have a secure connection, the Firefox address bar will show a lock icon with a red strike-through Fx89Padlock-RedLine.

If you enter a password on an insecure webpage, eavesdroppers or attackers could steal it. You will also see a warning message when you click inside the login box to enter a username or password.

Fx122InsecureLogin

Note: When you start entering your login information, the warning message can obscure the password entry box. To dismiss the warning, either press the Tab key or click the page background after you type in your username.

title: On a certain website, when I try to fill out their webform,  Firefox tells me to enter a valid e-mail address even though the e-mail address I have entered is valid
content: When I go to the website https://www.rebateinternational.com/RebateInternational/contactUs.do and I try to fill out the webform on that page and use autofill to fill in the e-mail address, it gives me an error message that says "please enter a valid email address" even though the e-mail address is valid. Also, if I do not use autofill, but simply type everything in manually, it still gives me that same error message. This problem does not occur in Google Chrome, but it does occur in Firefox. Sometimes I can solve the problem by erasing part of the email address and then re-typing that part, but that doesn't always work. It also doesn't work if I erase the entire e-mail address and type it in manually. The problem does not appear to be caused by add-ons and does not appear to be caused by hardware acceleration, because I have disabled add-ons and have turned off hardware acceleration. It also does not appear to be caused by cache and cookies, because the same problem occurs after I clear the cache and cookies. I will appreciate any response you can provide to help solve this problem.
